file_content.text: Officer? The monitor stations are down, and the area is secure.
I can't tell you how good it is to see you in person.
Now the Republic can mount a real defense without the Imps looking over their shoulders.
I'm going to get my squad out of here before anyone comes looking. Thanks for your help, though.
Your men seem pretty hurt; do you need help getting out?
Can you make it out safely?
They're tough. We'll make it, now that you've cleared the way.
Still, you've saved us and more importantly, you've poked a stick in the Empire's eye.
Somebody else might not have been good enough to save you.
You think pretty highly of yourself, but I guess you've earned the right to.
When the Republic makes its move, the Imps will never know it's coming. I'll look forward to seeing you there, friend.
